    <article class="p-optItem p-optItem--a" aria-label="Option A">
      <div class="p-optItem__inner">
        <h6 class="p-optItem__label" data-reveal-title>Option A</h6>

        <figure class="p-optItem__hero" data-reveal-body>
          <img class="p-optItem__heroImg" src="/assets/images/projects/blackbelt/option_a_hero.jpg" alt="Option A leaflet hero" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
        </figure>

        <div class="p-optItem__grid" data-reveal-body>
          <div class="p-optItem__col">
            <p>This concept prioritizes delivering all essential information required in the leaflet, including the opening schedule, educational programs, operating hours, and consultation details.</p>
            <p>Considering the information-heavy nature of offline leaflets, the layout was structured to ensure that each element does not compete for attention, with a strong focus on text hierarchy and overall layout organization.</p>
            <p>The roles of the headline, supporting copy, and detailed information were clearly defined, allowing the content to be read naturally from top to bottom even in a first-time viewing context.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="p-optItem__col">
            <p>The photo area was used as a secondary element to support understanding of the programs, positioned so that it does not interfere with the delivery of textual information and maintains clarity throughout the information search process.</p>
            <p class="p-optItem__strong">Option A presents a conservative and stable solution that prioritizes clarity and readability, fulfilling the fundamental role of the leaflet with a strong emphasis on effective information delivery.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="p-optItem p-optItem--b" aria-label="Option B">
      <div class="p-optItem__inner">
        <h6 class="p-optItem__label" data-reveal-title>Option B</h6>

        <figure class="p-optItem__hero" data-reveal-body>
          <img class="p-optItem__heroImg" src="/assets/images/projects/blackbelt/option_b_hero.jpg" alt="Option B leaflet hero" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
        </figure>

        <div class="p-optItem__grid" data-reveal-body>
          <div class="p-optItem__col">
            <p>This concept focuses on delivering the Grand Opening schedule and announcement as quickly and powerfully as possible.</p>
            <p>Large-scale headlines and strong color contrast were actively used to ensure that the “opening event” message is immediately recognized at first glance. Visual impact was prioritized, while unnecessary information was minimized so that the core message could be clearly conveyed even within a short exposure time.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="p-optItem__col">
            <p>Visual elements were arranged to emphasize the event atmosphere and a sense of dynamism, allowing the leaflet itself to be perceived as an event announcement. The structure was designed to draw rapid attention toward the event schedule and brand name.</p>
            <p class="p-optItem__strong">Option B prioritizes event awareness and visual attention, presenting a direction that responds most directly to the goal of announcing the opening through the leaflet.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="p-optItem p-optItem--c" aria-label="Option C">
      <div class="p-optItem__inner">
        <h6 class="p-optItem__label" data-reveal-title>Option C</h6>

        <figure class="p-optItem__hero" data-reveal-body>
          <img class="p-optItem__heroImg" src="/assets/images/projects/blackbelt/option_c_hero.jpg" alt="Option C leaflet hero" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
        </figure>

        <div class="p-optItem__grid" data-reveal-body>
          <div class="p-optItem__col">
            <p>This concept was designed to communicate both the opening announcement and educational credibility, with careful consideration given to balancing event-driven messaging and informational elements.</p>
            <p>The Grand Opening message is clearly positioned at the top to ensure immediate recognition of the opening, while the central area gradually introduces the academy’s educational direction and real activity imagery, naturally conveying the character and reliability of the taekwondo school.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="p-optItem__col">
            <p>Illustration elements were used to add visual approachability, allowing the design to feel accessible to both the target age group and parents. The overall layout and visual flow were structured around a progression from awareness to understanding and ultimately to consultation inquiries.</p>
            <p class="p-optItem__strong">Option C aims for the most balanced communication in an offline distribution environment, considering both the stability of information delivery and the visual impact of the opening announcement.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
